For the American government, there was no positive way out of this situation - it could not afford to throw the Shah overboard, as this would have severely damaged the confidence of its allies in other countries.
At the same time, she was unable to enforce the release of hostages in Iran, where the revolution led to the establishment of a theocratic regime.
It was a severe blow to the call of the united states, and the subsequent fiasco in the violent attempt of the hostage liberation made everything worse.
The captured diplomats were finally released after 444 days after negotiations by the Algerian government.
The fate of the hostages called home a wave of solidarity and anti-Iranian moods.
The debacle in Iran contributed significantly to Jimmy Carter's defeat against Ronald Reagan in the 1980 presidential elections.
The film Argo of the director and actor Ben Affleck describes an episode of this story that gave the United States a small partial victory.
Before occupying the message, six ambassadors managed to escape.
This ended after numerous complications in the residence of the Canadian ambassador.
The CIA, in cooperation with the Canadian authorities, managed to bring the refugees out of Iran, helping them an extravagant story to cover their true identity - they traveled with Canadian passports tarnished as members of a film staff that supposedly visited a science fiction film in the country.
Combination of genres
The plan developed by the expert on “Exfiltration - Tony Mendez” also required the collaboration of Hollywood.
