The details of this operation have long been kept secret. The film is based on Tony Mendez's memories.
Affleck's film is a special combination of several film genres.
On the one hand he is a realistic politician, but at the same time also a so-called “Caper Movie” i.e. the story of a successful Husar piece such as the film Ocean's Eleven.
In this way the mood levels change - on the one hand the documentary scenes from Tehran (in the title sequence iconic contemporary photographs are shown, and even in the film version of the same situations there are no major differences).
On the other hand, the loose passages from Hollywood, which come ironically and slightly overhead.
And then there are the scenes from the CIA headquarters and other institutions - men in suits at the meeting table, on the office halls, on the phone...
With this film Ben Affleck has succeeded in a remarkable restart of his career.
From a smiled actor has become a respectable director, and even as an actor he is now no longer the target of ironic remarks.
Argo is his third film after the crime No children's game (Gone Baby Gone, 2007) and the thriller city without grace (2010).
At the same time, it is Affleck's first film that does not play in the local Boston of the director.
The feeling for the atmosphere of the place was one of the characteristics that the previous films of this director were derived from the standard Hollywood.
However, this feeling also proves in Argo, where Tehran is \"played\" by Canada.
